  "narrative": "Summariser produced a numeric account balance not present in the source documents. The figure was plausible but fabricated. Detection came from a customer support ticket; the agent had been live in production for 8 hours before the first complaint. Root cause: the prompt allowed paraphrasing of numeric fields. The team rolled back the prompt, added a grounding constraint, and shipped an eval case asserting all numbers in output appear verbatim in input.",
  "fix_summary": "Prompt update: added 'numbers must appear verbatim in the source; if not, omit the number'. New eval case: tests/eval/test_numeric_grounding.py.",
  "eval_guard_added": {
    "path": "tests/eval/test_numeric_grounding.py",
    "description": "Asserts every digit-bearing token in summariser output appears in input chunk."
  },
  "follow_up_actions": [
    {"action": "Extend grounding rule to dates and email addresses", "owner": "alex@faion.net", "due_date": "2026-06-01"},
